@KingRoyalVR that's the whole problem with Abrams "mystery boxes".  They either don't get opened or when they do there's nothing in them.  It's absolutely abysmal storytelling that let's the audience down.  Once you've been fooled by him a couple of times more fool you if you invest your precious time into anything else he's involved with.

If you want to see how it should be done then go and watch Babylon 5, the grandfather of US story arc TV.  Mysteries and foreshadowing are in abundance, particularly in the early episodes, and they pretty much all pay off beautifully.

That's because J Michael Straczynski planned it out.  It wasn't just the story arcs but individual character arcs too and those weren't just for the main characters but for minor recurring ones.  He even put in the effort to figure out how these story and character arcs could be continued and resolved if an actor left the series, something which happened a couple of times.  It's a paradigm of how to plan out a story.

